-- Hong Kong Architects Chosen for West Kowloon Opera Center
-- B y   S a n d i   L i u
-- 2012-12-10T05:53:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/hong-kong-architects-chosen-for-west-kowloon-opera-center.html
The West Kowloon Cultural District
Authority appointed two Hong Kong-born architects for the design
of the Xiqu Centre, a landmark cultural venue for the district,
according to an e-mailed statement from the authority today.  Bing Thom in  Vancouver  and Ronald Lu of Hong Kong formed a
venture to work on the 13,800-square-meter site over the next
four years, according to the statement. The building will be the
first of 17 core arts and cultural venues to be opened in the
district, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sandi Liu in Hong Kong at 
